 <p class="philos"><span class="green">At the Adoption Shelter</span>
 <p>  At the shelter we house rabbits, rodents, guinea pigs, and ferrets we have taken in from local shelters where they were abandoned.  These shelters often do not have the space or
 the knowledge and resources to properly shelter these animals and may call us as a last resort before euthanizing them. <p> Most of them are healthy and  adoptable and our goal is to find forever homes for them.  For those who are sick are have other issues, we provide them with medical care and meet 
 their basic needs for food, water, and an enriched environment.  We need volunteers to:

<div class="greentext">
 <ul>
<li>  Socialize the rabbits to help them become more "adoptable"</span>
 <li> Play with the ferrets</span>
 <li>  Be part of a team to clean the living space of the shelter rabbits once a week
 <li>  Wash and dry the rabbits' laundry once a week
 </ul>
 </div>


 <p class="philos"><span class="orange">At the Sanctuary</span>
 <p>
 All of the rabbits at Rabbit Meadows Sanctuary are feral rabbits rescued from a variety of locations in the greater Seattle area. They have all been spayed and neutered and live naturally in family groups in a safe and protected environment.<p>

We need volunteers who love animals, are dependable and dont mind getting a little dirty.<p>

Good hygiene is essential to the health of the animals. A volunteer's work will primarily be cleaning up after them. This work is not glamorous, but it is critical to their health and well-being.  Positions available include:</P>

<div class="orangetext">
<ul>
<li>Cleaning rabbit runs and feeding fresh veggies (about 2 hours for two adults).  We ask for a commitment of one weekend day every 6-8 weeks. This can be a Saturday or Sunday, whichever you prefer.</span>
<span class="orangetext"><li> Help us move to our new location.</span>  
</ul>
</div>



<p class="philos"><span class="purple">Other Ways to Help</span>.

<div class="purptext">
<ul>
<li>Hold a fundraiser with BLRRFH as the designated charity (we will send you information and suggestions)
<li>Donate items for our shelter or sanctuary (see wish list)
<li>Serve on a committee to help direct the future of BLRRF!
</ul>
</div>

